<p>The <strong>World Community Grid</strong> (WCG) is an effort to create the world’s largest public computing grid to tackle scientific research projects. Using the idle time of computers around the world, the World Community Grid’s research projects have analyzed aspects of the human genome, HIV, dengue, muscular dystrophy, cancer, influenza, rice crop yields, and clean energy. Learn more at <a title="worldcommunitygrid.org" href="http://www.worldcommunitygrid.org/" target="_blank">worldcommunitygrid.org</a>.</p>
